T","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":69,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":78,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":89,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Cooke I was born in 1480, in Rustington, Sussex, England, his father, Thomas Cooke, was 30 and his mother, Elinor Barbor, was 25. He married Joane Howles in 1505, in Rustington, Sussex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1578, in Broadwater, Sussex, England, at the age of 98."},"et":{"1480–1578":"1480–1578","1490–1597":"1490–1597","1506–1582":"1506–1582","1450–Male":"1450–Surnud","1455–Female":"1455–Surnud","1450":"1450","1582":"1582","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1578":"1578","1455":"1455","1597":"1597","estimated 1506":"umbes 1506","20 September 1575":"20. september 1575","1506":"1506","15